maml:description.maml:para: Retrieves an authentication token from Wiz API using client credentials.

The Get-PSWizAuthenticationToken cmdlet sends a request to the Wiz authentication endpoint to retrieve an OAuth 2.0 access token. The cmdlet requires a Client ID and Client Secret to authenticate and obtain the token.
The Client ID for the Wiz application.
The Client Secret for the Wiz application.
The Client ID for the Wiz application.
The Client Secret for the Wiz application.

maml:alert.maml:para: The retrieved access token is stored in the global variable $Access_Token. The data center information extracted from the token is stored in the global variable $Data_Center.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- EXAMPLE 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: Get-PSWizAuthenticationToken -ClientID $ENV:Wiz_Client_ID -ClientSecret $Env:Client_Secret This example directly specifies the Client ID and Client Secret to retrieve an authentication token.
